OPEN (Apache-2.0) — the Poland member-state surfaces in surfaces/:
  panstwo (state), kraj (country), prezydent (president), min-cyfryzacji,
  ranking-organy (+EN), ranking-jst-kas (+EN).
This is the REFERENCE IMPLEMENTATION of the K0NSULT per-country layer; other
  EU member states instantiate the same pattern (see k0nsult-country-template).
NOT INCLUDED: the proprietary k0nsult.cloud engine (/api/* is the boundary);
  secrets/keys (No Password Custody).

PERSONAL DATA (GDPR/RODO) — honest scope: these transparency surfaces DO name
  public-office holders (e.g. ministers, heads of authorities, the President) in
  their OFFICIAL capacity. That is personal data of public figures, processed for a
  public-interest task and lawful under RODO art.6(1)(e)/(f). "agents-not-people"
  means NO SCORING/evaluation of natural persons — only public BODIES are ranked,
  never individuals. It does NOT claim the surfaces contain zero personal data.
  No private-individual PII, no special-category (art.9) data.

DOCTRINE: claim <= proof; Human Override Always; agents-not-people (no scoring of persons).
